/*
TC - O(1)
SC - O(1)

here we are dividing the number by 10 again and again until it becomes zero,
while dividing, each time the number's last digit getting removed.
and the new number that 

ex - 1898 -> 1898 / 10 = 189, count = 1
     189  -> 189 / 10 = 18, count = 2
     18   -> 18 / 10 = 1, count = 3
     1    -> 1 /  10 = 0, count = 4
     

*/
int countd(int n)
{
    int count = 0
    while(n > 0)
    {
        n = int(n/10);
        count += 1;
    }
    return count;
}
